  primary actors: System
                  Technition
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The system loads the modality worklist steps and patient information.
    2. Flags are displayed. (Flags are known conflicts)
      
    Alternative Flow:     
 
Charge Capture \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Patient
                  System
                  Secretary
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The system keeps track of the patients expenses.
    2. Expenses accrue as procedures are completed.
    3. The Patient interacts with the secretary to secure charge capture.
    
    Alternative flow:
    1. Patient contacts insurance and deducts their coverage from the total.
    
Modality image Archiving\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: System
                
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The system will automatically save all approved modality images and store them within an archival database 
    under the patient id and patient name
    2. The system amkes the recent aquistions available to PACS.
    
  Alternative Flow:   
    1a. If chosen, select images can be physically printed
    
Diagnositic Workstation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Radiologist
                  System
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The radiologist can select any image and view the image for diagnostics
    2. The radiologist writes their report.
    3. Radiologist requests to achrive report to Report Repository.
    
  Alternative Flow:   
    1a. If chosen, select images can be physically printed   
    
 Report Repository\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: System
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. Report is stored.
    2. Report is made available for viewing only, to the refering physcian
    
  Alternative Flow:   
    1a. If chosen, select images can be physically printed     
    
Secretary flags ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
  primary actors: Secretary
                  System
                  
    1. Secretary attempts to submit appointment.
    2. System alerts secretary to scheduling conflicts
    3. Secretary selects appropriate time with no conflicts.
    
Medical flags /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
   primary actors: technition
                   System
                   Refering physcian
                   
     1. Refering physcian request procedures.
     2. System catches known medical conflicts and throws the appropriate flags.
     3. These are soft flags. They will not stop the procedures, but alert the party involved.
     4. At procedure time Technition confirms flags are resolved.
     
Charge capture (financing) "splitting the bill" (Kyle Remillard, 2018)
  primary actors: System
                  Secretary
                  Patient
                  
      1. After each procedure is completed or each resource is expended a charge accrues on the patients bill.
      2. Check for insurance approval of expenses.
      3. The insurance is billed for the agreed upon amount and the patient's bill is reduced to the difference.
      4. The bill is made available for payment to patient by the scretary.

Orders filled ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
  primary actors: Secretary
                  System
    
    1. After appointment is submitted but not confirmed.
    2. Resource management system checks for available resources and scheduling conflicts.
    3. If successfull procedure is broken down into steps:
      Patient, follows pre-op guidelines
      modality checklist filled
      




